article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 61, SE Louisiana 57
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Devin Gibson scored 20 points to lead Texas-San Antonio to a 61-57 win over Southeastern Louisiana Thursday. Gibson hit 5-of-9 shots from the field and made 10-of-13 free throws. Melvin Smith added 16 points, hitting 6-of-13 shots from the field for UTSA (9-13, 3-6 Southland Conference). Antoine Dade grabbed a team-high six rebounds. Tavaris Nance led SLU (13-10, 5-5) with 14 points, Patrick Sullivan had 12 and Kevyn Green 10. The game was tied at 30 at halftime. The Roadrunners went on a 9-0 run to take the lead for good early in the second half.
